                <head>No. 363.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hoppin</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-08-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 28, 1879</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 361.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr. Welsh’s
                    No. 347 of the 13th instant, and to approve the prompt presentation of the
                    claims of the United States fishermen at Fortune Bay, which formed the subject
                    of Mr. Evarts’ No. 347 of the 1st instant.</p>
                <p>The additional copies of certain papers connected with the cases, which he thinks
                    it desirable to have transmitted, will be sent as soon as practicable.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
